Analysis Pipeline for "Adaptive Gridding for SNEC" (Fremling et al.)
=====================================================================

This directory contains all scripts needed to reproduce the tables and
figures in the paper.  Every table and figure is generated from scratch
by running SuperSNEC sweep configurations and computing RMS magnitude
residuals against the 1000-zone original SNEC reference.

Prerequisites:
  - SuperSNEC binary built:  make clean && make  (from repo root)
  - Python 3.10+ with numpy, scipy, matplotlib
  - Conda env:  source ~/miniconda3/etc/profile.d/conda.sh && conda activate skysurvey

Reference data (shipped in tmp/):
  - tmp/snec_original_1000z/lum_observed.dat   (1000-zone SNEC reference LC)
  - tmp/snec_original_100z/lum_observed.dat    (100-zone SNEC reference LC)

Shipped SN model comparisons (Figure 2):
  SN 2011dh (Ergon et al. 2014, 2015):
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn2011dh/obs_lbol.dat        (bolometric LC observations)
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn2011dh/obs_vel.dat          (Fe II 5169 velocity observations)
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn2011dh/.../gui_run_2145/Data/
      lum_observed.dat, vel_photo.dat                     (SuperSNEC model output)
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn2011dh/mesa_model_parameters.txt
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn2011dh/parameters_used.txt

  SN 1993J (Richmond et al. 1994; UNLV spectra):
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn1993j/SN1993J_bolometric_lc_uvoir_bb_*.csv
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn1993j/SN1993J_feii5169_velocity_from_unlv_*.csv
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn1993j/.../gui_run_2002/Data/
      lum_observed.dat, vel_photo.dat                     (SuperSNEC model output)
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn1993j/mesa_model_parameters.txt
  - Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn1993j/parameters_used.txt

  These are pre-computed model fits (not re-generated by the pipeline).


=== ONE-COMMAND FULL PIPELINE ===

  python3 Analysis/scripts/rebuild_all.py

This runs all sweeps, generates all 8 tables and 2 figures, and optionally
builds the paper PDF.  Total runtime: ~60-90 min depending on hardware.

Flags:
  --skip-sweeps   Skip SNEC runs; regenerate tables+figures from cached TSV data.
  --skip-pdf      Do not build the paper PDF (default: builds if latexmk found).
  --python PATH   Use a specific Python interpreter.
  --latexmk PATH  Use a specific latexmk binary.


=== SCRIPTS AND THEIR OUTPUTS ===

Scripts are organized in three tiers: (1) sweep runners that execute SNEC,
(2) table generators that read TSV and write LaTeX, and (3) figure generators.

--- Sweep Scripts (Phase 1) ---

Each sweep script writes parameters, runs ./snec for each case, parses log
output, computes RMS metrics, and writes results to a TSV file under
Analysis/results/<sweep_name>/results.tsv.

1. run_imax_scaling_scan.py
   Purpose:  Zone-count scaling (N=60..1000) and quadrature convergence scan.
             Runs SNEC and saves LCs + runtimes; tables generated separately
             by generate_imax_scaling_table.py.
   Output:   tmp/lum_baseline_imax{N}.dat, tmp/lum_quad_np{n}.dat,
             tmp/imax_scan_runtimes.tsv, tmp/quad_scan_runtimes.tsv
   Cases:    6 imax values x 3 timing runs + 7 quad values x 3 timing runs = 39 runs
   Runtime:  ~25 min
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/run_imax_scaling_scan.py

2. run_cumulative_speedup.py
   Purpose:  Cumulative speedup benchmark (12 configs, each adding one optimization).
   Output:   Analysis/results/cumulative_speedup/results.tsv
             Paper/generated/table_cumulative_speedup.tex (Table 2)
   Cases:    12 configs (3 original SNEC = shipped data, 9 SuperSNEC x 3 runs each)
   Runtime:  ~5 min
   Flags:
     --skip-reference   Reuse cached 1000-zone result (already shipped).
     --force            Force re-run of all cached configurations.
     --supersnec-only   Skip original SNEC runs (use shipped reference data).
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/run_cumulative_speedup.py

3. run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py
   Purpose:  Solver-threshold sweep: EPSTOL (1e-8 to 2e-3) and ITMAX (100/300
             to 2/6) in adaptive_runtime mode (Tables 3 and 4).
   Output:   Analysis/results/solver_threshold/results.tsv (34 cases)
   Flags:
     --case-filter REGEX   Run only cases matching the pattern.
     --timeout-s SECS      Per-case timeout (default 120s).
   Runtime:  ~10 min
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py

4. run_ni_cadence_grid_mode_comparison.py
   Purpose:  Cross-mode Ni cadence comparison (adaptive_runtime vs legacy_pattern).
   Output:   Analysis/results/ni_cadence_grid_mode_comparison/results.tsv
   Cases:    14 (7 f_Ni values x 2 grid modes)
   Runtime:  ~5 min
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/run_ni_cadence_grid_mode_comparison.py

5. run_remap_scheduling_sweep.py
   Purpose:  Remap scheduling modes (0, -1, -2, -3) at 4 base intervals.
   Output:   Analysis/results/remap_scheduling/results.tsv
   Cases:    16 (4 modes x 4 intervals), 3 runs each for median timing
   Runtime:  ~15 min
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/run_remap_scheduling_sweep.py

6. run_legacy_ni_cadence_2d_sweep.py
   Purpose:  2D legacy-pattern Ni cadence sweep (f_Ni x Ni_period_max).
   Output:   Analysis/results/legacy_ni_cadence_2d/results.tsv
   Cases:    36 (6 f_Ni values x 6 Ni_period_max values)
   Runtime:  ~15 min
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/run_legacy_ni_cadence_2d_sweep.py

--- Table Generators (Phase 2) ---

7. generate_imax_scaling_table.py
   Purpose:  Generate Tables 1 and 5 from cached imax/quad scan data.
   Input:    tmp/lum_baseline_imax{N}.dat, tmp/lum_quad_np{n}.dat, runtimes TSVs
   Output:   Paper/generated/table_imax_scaling.tex (Table 1)
             Paper/generated/table_quad_convergence.tex (Table 5)
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/generate_imax_scaling_table.py

8. generate_paper_tables.py
   Purpose:  Generate Tables 3, 4, 6, 7, 8 from sweep TSV results.
   Input:    Analysis/results/solver_threshold/results.tsv
             Analysis/results/ni_cadence_grid_mode_comparison/results.tsv
             Analysis/results/remap_scheduling/results.tsv
             Analysis/results/legacy_ni_cadence_2d/results.tsv
   Output:   Paper/generated/table_solver_itmax_only.tex (Table 3)
             Paper/generated/table_solver_epstol_only.tex (Table 4)
             Paper/generated/table_ni_cadence_comparison.tex (Table 6)
             Paper/generated/table_remap_scheduling.tex (Table 7)
             Paper/generated/table_legacy_ni_cadence.tex (Table 8)
   Command:
     python3 Analysis/scripts/generate_paper_tables.py

--- Figure Generators (Phase 3) ---

9.  plot_adaptive_runtime_validation.py
    Purpose:  Figure 1 -- adaptive-runtime validation LC comparison.
    Input:    tmp/snec_original_1000z/lum_observed.dat (shipped)
              tmp/snec_original_100z/lum_observed.dat (shipped)
              Runs 3 SuperSNEC configs (cached in tmp/fig1_*.dat)
    Output:   Analysis/figures/adaptive_runtime_validation.png
    Command:
      python3 Analysis/scripts/plot_adaptive_runtime_validation.py

10. plot_lc_comparison_sne.py
    Purpose:  Figure 2 -- SN 2011dh and SN 1993J model comparison.
    Input:    Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn2011dh/ (shipped model + obs data)
              Analysis/lc_comparisons/sn1993j/ (shipped model + obs data)
    Output:   Analysis/figures/lc_comparison_sne.pdf
    Command:
      python3 Analysis/scripts/plot_lc_comparison_sne.py

--- Shared Utility ---

11. snec_metrics.py
    Purpose:  Shared library imported by all sweep/table scripts.
    Provides: BASELINE_PARAMETERS, write_parameters_file(), compute_mag_metrics(),
              read_lum(), write_tsv(), run_cmd(), parse_log_indicators(),
              count_nan_in_lum()
    Not called directly.


=== PAPER TABLE/FIGURE MAPPING ===

  Table 1  (imax scaling)          <- run_imax_scaling_scan.py + generate_imax_scaling_table.py
  Table 2  (cumulative speedup)    <- run_cumulative_speedup.py (self-generates table)
  Table 3  (solver ITMAX)          <- run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py + generate_paper_tables.py
  Table 4  (solver EPSTOL)         <- run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py + generate_paper_tables.py
  Table 5  (quad convergence)      <- run_imax_scaling_scan.py + generate_imax_scaling_table.py
  Table 6  (Ni cadence comparison) <- run_ni_cadence_grid_mode_comparison.py + generate_paper_tables.py
  Table 7  (remap scheduling)      <- run_remap_scheduling_sweep.py + generate_paper_tables.py
  Table 8  (legacy Ni cadence)     <- run_legacy_ni_cadence_2d_sweep.py + generate_paper_tables.py
  Figure 1 (adaptive validation)   <- plot_adaptive_runtime_validation.py
  Figure 2 (SN comparison)         <- plot_lc_comparison_sne.py


=== REGENERATING FROM CACHED DATA ===

If sweeps have already been run and TSV results exist, regenerate only
tables and figures with:

  python3 Analysis/scripts/rebuild_all.py --skip-sweeps

Or regenerate individual tables:

  python3 Analysis/scripts/generate_imax_scaling_table.py     # Tables 1, 5
  python3 Analysis/scripts/generate_paper_tables.py           # Tables 3, 4, 6, 7, 8

Or individual figures:

  python3 Analysis/scripts/plot_adaptive_runtime_validation.py  # Figure 1
  python3 Analysis/scripts/plot_lc_comparison_sne.py            # Figure 2

Note: Figure 1 runs 3 SuperSNEC configs on first call and caches results
in tmp/fig1_*.dat. Delete these files to force re-runs.


=== FORCING RE-RUNS ===

To force a complete re-run from scratch:

  rm -rf Analysis/results/*/results.tsv tmp/lum_baseline_imax*.dat tmp/lum_quad_np*.dat
  rm -rf tmp/imax_scan_runtimes.tsv tmp/quad_scan_runtimes.tsv
  rm -rf tmp/fig1_*.dat
  python3 Analysis/scripts/rebuild_all.py

Individual sweep re-runs:

  # Re-run solver threshold sweep only
  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_adaptive_threshold_limits.py

  # Re-run cumulative speedup (force all configs)
  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_cumulative_speedup.py --force

  # Re-run imax scaling scan
  python3 Analysis/scripts/run_imax_scaling_scan.py


=== CACHING BEHAVIOR ===

- run_cumulative_speedup.py: Caches per-config results as .npz files in
  Analysis/results/cumulative_speedup/{outdir_name}/result.npz.
  Use --force to re-run all. Original SNEC results (configs 0-2) are
  shipped as reference data and cannot be re-generated.

- run_imax_scaling_scan.py: Overwrites tmp/lum_baseline_imax{N}.dat and
  tmp/imax_scan_runtimes.tsv on every run (no cache check).

- plot_adaptive_runtime_validation.py: Caches SuperSNEC runs as
  tmp/fig1_{label}.dat. Delete to force re-run.

- All other sweep scripts: Overwrite their results.tsv on every run.


